WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:07.161
<i>* Xk</i>

00:07.200 --> 00:10.033
Stella: Aww!
Look at these two.

00:10.070 --> 00:15.031
She's been dreaming about this
day since she was a sapling.

00:15.080 --> 00:18.209
He's got a tiny stick
up his butt.

00:18.250 --> 00:21.777
But you can't deny they
were made for each other.

00:21.820 --> 00:23.242
Stella?

00:23.290 --> 00:24.815
Hmm?
Who are you talking to?

00:24.850 --> 00:26.181
Oh.

00:26.220 --> 00:27.187
Thought
I was talking to you.

00:27.220 --> 00:30.190
Oh, let me guess.
You two need a wedding cake.

00:30.230 --> 00:34.224
Actually, we need
a funeral cake.

00:34.260 --> 00:35.557
That's not a thing.
Right.

00:35.600 --> 00:39.298
But I love cake,
and it's my funeral.

00:39.340 --> 00:41.434
My living funeral.

00:41.470 --> 00:42.801
I'm dying.

00:42.840 --> 00:45.639
Wow. I'm so sorry.

00:45.670 --> 00:46.671
Oh, no, don't be.

00:46.710 --> 00:49.441
My life has been
pretty amazing.

00:49.480 --> 00:52.575
I can honestly say
I wouldn't change a thing.

00:52.620 --> 00:54.645
Stella: From the minute I was
diagnosed with cancer,

00:54.680 --> 00:57.149
my mom and dad were there
for me no matter what.

00:57.190 --> 01:00.251
We're here for you.
No matter what.

01:00.290 --> 01:01.280
* I've been thinking

01:01.320 --> 01:03.220
Over the next few years,

01:03.260 --> 01:08.221
my brother Aiden encouraged me
to live like I was dying.

01:08.260 --> 01:10.160
* Just waiting

01:10.200 --> 01:11.759
Because I was.

01:11.800 --> 01:13.461
Yeah!

01:13.500 --> 01:17.835
My sister Elizabeth
never let me miss a beat...

01:17.870 --> 01:21.170
even when I was
at my absolute worst.

01:21.210 --> 01:24.145
<i>* Xk</i>

01:24.180 --> 01:28.447
My family always
helped me face my fears.

01:28.480 --> 01:31.541
So that dying would seem
like the next great adventure.

01:33.460 --> 01:35.554
Woman: Would you do something
for me?

01:35.590 --> 01:38.252
Six years in, I thought
I had done it all.

01:38.290 --> 01:40.156
Would you get me
out of here?

01:40.200 --> 01:42.464
But then I was watching
this sappy cancer movie

01:42.500 --> 01:44.798
with my sister
and her husband, Diego,

01:44.830 --> 01:46.832
and I realized that there
was still one thing

01:46.870 --> 01:48.338
left for me to do --

01:48.370 --> 01:50.862
find true love.

01:50.910 --> 01:52.036
So after I stopped chemo,

01:52.070 --> 01:55.176
my dad scraped together
the money to send me

01:55.210 --> 01:57.178
to the birthplace of love --

01:57.210 --> 01:58.177
Paris.

01:58.210 --> 02:01.316
* Waiting on a song

02:01.350 --> 02:07.483
<i>* Xk</i>

02:07.520 --> 02:09.750
Where I dressed up
like a sexy mime

02:09.789 --> 02:13.829
and waited for my soul mate
to appear.

02:13.860 --> 02:16.192
Both: Oh! I'm so sorry.

02:16.230 --> 02:18.392
He was lost -- literally.

02:18.430 --> 02:19.693
Can you help me?

02:19.740 --> 02:22.334
But he was also
figuratively lost.

02:22.370 --> 02:24.634
See, he was
afraid to live...

02:24.670 --> 02:26.604
Wes:
And she was afraid to die.

02:26.640 --> 02:29.177
Oh, baby, you've gotta
stop adding that part.

02:29.210 --> 02:31.304
I was not afraid to die.

02:31.350 --> 02:32.545
We'll just tell it
your way.

02:32.580 --> 02:36.642
So there we were,
two strangers in Paris...

02:36.690 --> 02:38.579
falling in love the way
only two people

02:38.620 --> 02:41.351
with nothing else
to do truly can.

02:41.390 --> 02:46.954
<i>* Xk</i>

02:47.000 --> 02:52.530
<i>* Xk</i>

02:52.570 --> 02:54.789
* Running through the heat,
heartbeat *

02:54.840 --> 02:58.333
* You shine like silver
in the sunlight *

02:58.370 --> 03:00.702
* You light up my whole heart

03:00.740 --> 03:03.209
* It feels like in the sun

03:03.250 --> 03:05.571
You know what happens next.

03:05.610 --> 03:11.811
* Love like this
won't last forever *

03:11.850 --> 03:18.381
* T know that love like this
won't last forever *

03:18.430 --> 03:21.730
* But I --
I don't really mind *

03:21.760 --> 03:24.730
<i>* Xk</i>

03:24.770 --> 03:26.568
Stella?

03:26.600 --> 03:29.638
Will you spend
the rest of your life...

03:29.670 --> 03:32.310
with me?

03:32.340 --> 03:33.273
I love you.

03:33.310 --> 03:35.870
I love you, too.

03:35.910 --> 03:39.369
* Forever, but I

03:39.420 --> 03:40.512
* Yeah

03:40.550 --> 03:43.588
So I got my godmother Poppy
to marry us.

03:43.620 --> 03:45.588
Sure, getting married
was a rash decision,

03:45.620 --> 03:48.453
but it was only a six-
to eight-month commitment tops.

03:48.490 --> 03:50.584
-I love you.
-Not yet!

03:50.630 --> 03:54.453
"Husband and wife,"
I have to say that part.

03:54.500 --> 03:58.266
And so began
the sexiest marriage ever.

03:58.300 --> 04:01.270
* You

04:01.300 --> 04:02.529
I know what you're thinking.

04:02.570 --> 04:05.835
Nobody has Sara Bareilles
candle sex every night.

04:05.870 --> 04:07.338
But we do.

04:07.380 --> 04:08.734
Because we never know

04:08.780 --> 04:11.772
if it will be my
last night on earth.

04:11.810 --> 04:14.745
That was a beautiful story.

04:14.780 --> 04:16.418
A little longer
than I expected,

04:16.450 --> 04:19.010
but...a beautiful story.

04:19.050 --> 04:22.782
You're life is like one of
those romantic cancer movies.

04:22.830 --> 04:27.028
I want to give you
a free cake.

04:27.060 --> 04:29.290
Thank you so much.

04:29.330 --> 04:31.697
Okay.
I played the cancer card,

04:31.730 --> 04:34.438
but you have to play
the hand you're dealt.

04:34.470 --> 04:37.804
After all, I am dying.

04:37.840 --> 04:39.069
You're not dying.

04:39.110 --> 04:41.602
I'm sorry.

04:41.640 --> 04:43.472
What did you just say?

04:43.510 --> 04:45.877
The oncolytic
virotherapy worked.

04:45.910 --> 04:47.912
Stella...

04:47.950 --> 04:49.349
you're cured.

04:49.390 --> 04:51.882
Oh, my God!
That's amazing!

04:51.920 --> 04:53.786
That's amazing!
Thank you so much!

04:53.820 --> 04:57.427
* Your yelling's
getting loud *

04:57.460 --> 04:59.394
* Keep it down now

04:59.430 --> 05:02.422
* Keep it down now

05:02.470 --> 05:06.338
* There's talk going
'round this town *

05:06.370 --> 05:07.895
* Keep it down now

05:07.940 --> 05:09.806
Needless to say,
my living funeral

05:09.840 --> 05:11.569
took on a whole new meaning.

05:11.610 --> 05:13.738
* Noises closing in
from all sides *

05:13.780 --> 05:15.703
* Warning all the ways to die

05:15.740 --> 05:17.071
Stella:
I know that we've been

05:17.110 --> 05:19.909
down this road before...

05:19.950 --> 05:23.887
Dr. Chang said that
I'm not in remission...

05:23.920 --> 05:26.480
I'm cured.

05:27.520 --> 05:28.385
Man:
I don't believe it.

05:28.420 --> 05:36.420
<i>* Xk</i>

05:36.630 --> 05:39.497
Oh, Daddy, stop crying.

05:39.540 --> 05:40.894
You're making me cry.

05:40.940 --> 05:42.430
Your mom's
not gonna stop.

05:42.470 --> 05:45.508
I'm so glad
you're okay.

05:45.540 --> 05:46.905
Thank you.

05:46.940 --> 05:47.873
Who are you?

05:47.910 --> 05:49.446
Oh, I'm Aiden's friend
Marlene.

05:49.480 --> 05:53.110
She's here for
emotional support.

05:53.150 --> 05:56.074
<i>* Xk</i>

05:56.120 --> 05:59.488
* C'est la vie *

05:59.520 --> 06:01.557
We got rowdy that night.

06:01.590 --> 06:03.649
Even Dad danced.

06:03.690 --> 06:06.728
* C'est la vie *

06:06.760 --> 06:11.061
* It's unforgettable

06:11.100 --> 06:12.932
<i>* Xk</i>

06:12.970 --> 06:14.438
Diego:
All right, hey, guys!

06:14.470 --> 06:16.404
Why are we still
holding these eulogies

06:16.440 --> 06:17.339
for someone
who's not dying?

06:17.370 --> 06:19.429
Why don't we just
burn this thing, huh?

06:19.480 --> 06:20.606
Who's with me?
Come on!

06:20.640 --> 06:24.008
This thing is not lighting.
Okay, just give me a second.

06:24.050 --> 06:26.417
All right, okay.
Okay, fine, fine, fine.

06:26.450 --> 06:28.976
Okay.

06:29.020 --> 06:31.614
Oh, Stel, you should have
invited Dr. Chang

06:31.650 --> 06:32.879
so we could have
thanked her in person.

06:32.920 --> 06:36.879
Mmm. Oh, this
was just for family.

06:36.930 --> 06:40.560
And apparently, Marlene.
-Aww!

06:40.600 --> 06:41.556
Plus, I was thinking
that I could --

06:41.600 --> 06:43.796
I could throw Dr. Chang
her own party next week

06:43.830 --> 06:47.539
instead of family dinner.
Of course, yes!

06:47.570 --> 06:48.765
So...
what are you gonna do

06:48.800 --> 06:50.939
with the first day of
the rest of your life?

06:50.970 --> 06:53.871
I don't know.
Maybe I'll apply to college.

06:53.910 --> 06:58.541
I know a professor who could
write me a good recommendation.

07:00.150 --> 07:01.618
Everything okay, Daddy?

07:01.650 --> 07:04.813
Yep. Never been better,
Stel-belle.

07:04.850 --> 07:11.654
<i>* Xk</i>

07:11.690 --> 07:13.522
Hey, did my dad
seem weird to you?

07:13.560 --> 07:16.621
No, you're dad's
just not a very emotional guy.

07:16.670 --> 07:19.640
Yeah.
It's probably nothing.

07:19.670 --> 07:23.561
Okay, time for our
private celebration.

07:23.610 --> 07:26.534
Play Sara Bareilles.

07:28.580 --> 07:32.642
MmMmm.

07:32.680 --> 07:35.547
Mmm. Actually...
Mm

07:35.580 --> 07:37.241
Um...

07:37.290 --> 07:41.659
would you mind
if we took the night off?

07:41.690 --> 07:43.727
I'm -- I'm exhausted, and-- Yes.

07:43.760 --> 07:46.491
Absolutely fine.
No problem.

07:46.530 --> 07:47.929
Okay. I'm sorry.

07:47.960 --> 07:51.225
Today's just...
been a lot.

07:51.270 --> 07:52.692
And I...

07:52.740 --> 07:53.969
don't want
to be up for hours.

07:54.000 --> 07:55.490
Babe, it doesn't
have to take hours.

07:55.540 --> 07:58.510
I mean, maybe we can just
ditch the 600 candles

07:58.540 --> 07:59.302
and the indie-rock
soundtrack

07:59.340 --> 08:02.139
and, you know,
just get 'er done.

08:02.180 --> 08:03.579
Oh. Ow.

08:03.610 --> 08:06.648
Am I the "er" in
that crude proposition?

08:06.680 --> 08:08.739
Oh, no. I mean, yes,
you are, but I--

08:08.780 --> 08:10.043
Do you not like
the way we have sex?

08:10.090 --> 08:11.910
I love it. It's not that,
I'm just saying

08:11.950 --> 08:14.612
that this isn't gonna be
your last night on earth,

08:14.660 --> 08:17.527
so maybe
we could change it up.

08:17.560 --> 08:19.699
I don't want anything
to change.

08:21.700 --> 08:23.919
You know what? Never mind.
Let's just go to bed.

08:29.640 --> 08:31.938
What are you doing?

08:31.970 --> 08:34.530
I always fall asleep
with my head on your chest.

08:34.580 --> 08:38.140
Unless you don't like being
my pillow anymore, either.

08:38.179 --> 08:41.548
No, I --I love
being your pillow.

08:41.580 --> 08:44.015
Get in there.

08:46.050 --> 08:47.449
Yeah.

08:47.490 --> 08:51.586
As I lay there, I could feel
things were already changing,

08:51.630 --> 08:53.758
I just didn't know how much.

08:53.800 --> 08:55.723
What?
-Hi, Daddy.

08:55.760 --> 08:59.094
Oh. Just came to see
how you were doing.

08:59.130 --> 09:01.861
Can't talk, Stel-belle,
late for my lecture.

09:01.900 --> 09:05.962
-Oh.
-Rent's on the counter.

09:06.010 --> 09:07.671
Love you.

09:07.710 --> 09:10.543
What's going on?

09:12.750 --> 09:15.173
Mom just left Dad.

09:17.090 --> 09:19.752
Do you --
Do you want a waffle?

09:24.730 --> 09:26.596
Aiden:
These waffles are amazing.

09:26.630 --> 09:28.098
You should try it.

09:28.130 --> 09:29.894
Can you just stop
with the waffle?

09:29.930 --> 09:31.864
You're right, this is serious.
A waffle isn't the answer.

09:31.900 --> 09:33.834
Oh, I also have three flavors
of Tasty Strudel--

09:33.870 --> 09:37.261
Will someone just
tell me what happened?

09:37.310 --> 09:39.267
Lizzie, you take it.

09:39.310 --> 09:40.937
Oh, okay.

09:40.980 --> 09:45.702
The way Mom and Dad
act around you is a show.

09:45.750 --> 09:47.013
They've got problems.

09:47.050 --> 09:48.814
They just
kept them from you

09:48.850 --> 09:50.944
because Dr. Chang
told us not to dump in,

09:50.990 --> 09:53.960
because creating a positive
emotional environment

09:53.990 --> 09:56.789
would give you a better shot
at beating cancer.

09:56.830 --> 09:58.719
So...

09:58.760 --> 10:01.320
we all kept stuff
from you.

10:01.360 --> 10:03.021
You all have...

10:03.070 --> 10:05.892
secrets you've been hiding from
me for the last eight years?

10:05.930 --> 10:07.637
Oh, uh...
-No, no secrets.

10:07.670 --> 10:09.092
I'm good.

10:09.140 --> 10:10.630
Are you lying?

10:10.670 --> 10:13.708
Obviously.
Aiden is stress-eating.

10:13.740 --> 10:15.834
So what are you're problems?

10:15.880 --> 10:19.100
Uh, Aiden is a grown man
who still lives at home,

10:19.150 --> 10:21.710
sells his ADD medication
to soccer moms,

10:21.750 --> 10:25.118
and uses your cancer to guilt
them into sleeping with him.

10:25.150 --> 10:28.711
Well, Elizabeth hates
her children. I do not!

10:28.760 --> 10:31.650
Please, you said that you would
trade them for a massage chair.

10:31.690 --> 10:33.124
I said that once.

10:33.160 --> 10:36.152
Okay, okay.
I will admit I...

10:36.200 --> 10:37.725
made sacrifices
in my career

10:37.770 --> 10:39.864
so that I could have
children early

10:39.900 --> 10:43.666
to give Mom and Dad
something positive to focus on.

10:43.710 --> 10:45.337
And I may regret that.

10:45.370 --> 10:48.908
And I may regret selling drugs
and sleeping with soccer moms.

10:48.940 --> 10:52.342
-No! It's so fun!

10:52.380 --> 10:55.111
Guys,
I do what I have to.

10:55.150 --> 10:57.016
Dad gives handouts
to his dying daughter,

10:57.050 --> 10:58.916
but all he gives
his loser son is grief.

10:58.950 --> 11:01.681
And a place to live.
Reluctantly.

11:01.720 --> 11:02.926
He gives that
reluctantly.

11:02.960 --> 11:07.158
Okay, you...
might be beyond help.

11:07.200 --> 11:08.827
But, Lizzie...

11:08.860 --> 11:12.421
if you need to focus on work,
I can babysit.

11:12.470 --> 11:14.734
You know nothing about
kids. That's not true.

11:14.770 --> 11:15.760
I know a lot.

11:15.800 --> 11:17.837
I believe...

11:17.870 --> 11:19.975
the children are our future.

11:20.010 --> 11:21.739
That sounds about right.

11:21.780 --> 11:24.408
I do have a stupid client
dinner tomorrow night and--

11:24.450 --> 11:27.044
Done!
Oh.

11:27.080 --> 11:28.741
I probably should
have run that by Wes,

11:28.780 --> 11:30.919
but I figured
he'd be cool with it.

11:30.950 --> 11:32.759
He loves to make me happy.

11:32.790 --> 11:33.985
I mean,
the past six months,

11:34.020 --> 11:36.318
I did whatever it took
to make her happy,

11:36.360 --> 11:38.749
even when it didn't
always make me happy.

11:38.790 --> 11:39.791
Now I'm starting to worry

11:39.830 --> 11:42.356
if I can keep it up
for the rest of our lives.

11:42.400 --> 11:43.822
Uh, you see, Wes,

11:43.870 --> 11:45.895
this is a support group

11:45.930 --> 11:48.490
for the spouses
of the terminally ill,

11:48.540 --> 11:50.201
which you no longer are.

11:50.240 --> 11:55.235
That's why we ordered you
this celebratory pizza.

11:55.280 --> 11:58.409
Ah, you guy!
You're the best.

11:58.450 --> 12:00.873
Just before we dig into it,
though, can I ask you--

12:00.920 --> 12:02.069
No. No.

12:02.120 --> 12:05.750
Wes, this pizza is a...

12:05.790 --> 12:07.781
it's a gesture of...

12:07.820 --> 12:09.822
good-bye.

12:09.860 --> 12:12.955
It's a good-bye pizza.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.128
Yeah. Let's eat.

12:15.160 --> 12:19.290
<i>* Xk</i>

12:19.330 --> 12:21.094
I knew that my dad
wasn't the type of guy

12:21.140 --> 12:23.768
that was gonna tell me
what was going on,

12:23.810 --> 12:25.437
so I went to him.

12:25.470 --> 12:31.500
<i>* Xk</i>

12:31.550 --> 12:34.019
Hey, Daddy.
Stel-belle.

12:34.050 --> 12:36.178
What are you doing here?

12:36.220 --> 12:38.882
Can we talk about
you and Mom?

12:38.920 --> 12:40.911
We're fine.
She left you.

12:40.960 --> 12:44.180
We've been better.

12:44.230 --> 12:46.551
I know
you want to protect me.

12:46.590 --> 12:48.490
Lizzie told me about
the whole dumping in thing

12:48.530 --> 12:50.919
while Aiden claimed you
thought he was a loser.

12:50.970 --> 12:52.426
He is a loser.

12:52.470 --> 12:55.496
He spent an entire week hiding
our garden gnomes in places

12:55.540 --> 12:58.510
that would scare me
in the dark.

12:58.540 --> 12:59.939
That's...

12:59.980 --> 13:01.129
not funny.

13:02.910 --> 13:06.813
Dad, you don't have to
protect me anymore.

13:06.850 --> 13:09.945
Just tell me what happened.
Why did Mom leave?

13:09.990 --> 13:12.140
She's just staying
at Poppy's for a while

13:12.190 --> 13:16.013
while she processes
the fact...

13:16.060 --> 13:18.449
we may have to
sell the house.

13:18.490 --> 13:19.889
Why?

13:19.930 --> 13:22.126
I can't afford
the mortgage.

13:22.160 --> 13:23.867
Or the second mortgage.

13:23.900 --> 13:27.268
Well, if you were hurting,
why didn't you say something?

13:27.300 --> 13:31.840
You didn't have to pay
for Paris or my wedding.

13:31.870 --> 13:32.837
Or my rent.

13:32.880 --> 13:38.000
No, I don't regret
helping you for one second.

13:38.050 --> 13:39.609
But I should have been
more responsible

13:39.650 --> 13:41.140
with how much I helped.

13:41.180 --> 13:44.013
I should have told
your mother sooner.

13:45.590 --> 13:47.251
For the first time
in my life,

13:47.290 --> 13:50.123
my dad needed my help
more than I needed his.

13:50.160 --> 13:52.379
Here's what we're gonna do.
I'll talk to Mom,

13:52.430 --> 13:55.593
and you are gonna figure out
how to save the house.

13:55.630 --> 14:00.534
And to help, I am cutting
myself off financially,

14:00.570 --> 14:01.992
starting right now.

14:02.040 --> 14:03.929
Rent check...

14:03.970 --> 14:05.506
What about college?

14:05.540 --> 14:07.008
College is for dorks.

14:07.040 --> 14:09.338
I'm a college professor.

14:09.380 --> 14:11.439
I'll get a job.

14:11.480 --> 14:14.415
So I did the same thing
every desperate Millennial

14:14.450 --> 14:17.988
with a funky haircut does,
I became a barista.

14:18.020 --> 14:20.057
Never show up
without the hat.

14:20.090 --> 14:23.060
Yes! My first job ever!

14:23.090 --> 14:24.888
Was it my dream job?

14:24.930 --> 14:27.126
No. But it was a start.

14:27.160 --> 14:28.889
And now that I was
pulling my own weight,

14:28.930 --> 14:30.523
I thought it would be
a good time for me

14:30.570 --> 14:33.267
to go by my godmother's house
and talk to my mom.

14:33.300 --> 14:40.502
<i>* Xk</i>

14:40.540 --> 14:42.406
I thought wrong.

14:45.950 --> 14:47.247
As I watched
my mother make up

14:47.280 --> 14:49.442
for missing 30 years
