I don't love
being your pillow.

28:21.300 --> 28:23.052
It is nice for a minute,

28:23.100 --> 28:25.819
but then my arm falls asleep
and there's a real chance

28:25.870 --> 28:27.793
I'm developing
permanent nerve damage.

28:27.840 --> 28:29.194
If I can't lift
my hands above my head,

28:29.240 --> 28:30.799
how am I ever gonna
wash my hair?

28:30.840 --> 28:33.229
Well, you know what,
it's not important.

28:34.940 --> 28:37.272
What is important is...

28:38.980 --> 28:40.209
...I love you.

28:40.250 --> 28:43.709
And I'm so sorry
that I have lied to you.

28:46.820 --> 28:48.914
Can you ever forgive me?

28:48.960 --> 28:51.827
I couldn't answer
because I didn't know.

28:51.860 --> 28:54.227
Stella?
I didn't know him.

28:54.260 --> 28:57.025
Hey, little sis,
back yard is all done.

28:57.060 --> 28:58.494
Apparently,
I do decorate.

28:58.530 --> 29:01.761
Marlene is finishing up some
fabulous little centerpiece.

29:01.800 --> 29:04.303
Why is Marlene here? You
invited her at your funeral.

29:04.340 --> 29:06.866
I told you I was setting you up
with Dr. Chang tonight.

29:06.910 --> 29:08.400
Does Dr. Chang know that?

29:08.440 --> 29:10.772
-Yes.
-Yikes!

29:10.810 --> 29:12.107
Uh, well,
this is awkward.

29:12.150 --> 29:15.176
Good evening,
party people.

29:15.220 --> 29:16.517
Oh.

29:18.290 --> 29:20.110
Oh!
This is a bag of poop!

29:20.150 --> 29:21.857
-Yep.
-I tried to stop her.

29:21.890 --> 29:24.382
It's a little thank you for
your wonderful work babysitting.

29:24.430 --> 29:26.558
Leaving that dinner
cost my firm the client,

29:26.590 --> 29:28.490
so happy ring hunting.

29:28.530 --> 29:31.921
Could tonight get
any worse?

29:31.970 --> 29:34.337
Hello, family.
Really?

29:34.370 --> 29:35.997
Poppy,
what are you doing here?

29:36.040 --> 29:37.030
You invited me
at your funeral.

29:37.070 --> 29:38.868
You invited everyone.

29:38.910 --> 29:41.333
And she's my date.

29:41.380 --> 29:43.007
Your date?
Did I miss something?

29:43.040 --> 29:44.906
Uh,
I -- I definitely did.

29:44.950 --> 29:46.941
Oh, Mom has decided
to be a bi with Poppy.

29:46.980 --> 29:49.347
We don't have to put
labels on it, but...

29:49.380 --> 29:52.145
we recently upped the level
of physical intimacy.

29:52.190 --> 29:53.919
Uh.
That was an over-share.

29:53.960 --> 29:56.156
No, please, regale us
all with tales

29:56.190 --> 29:57.828
of your progressive
lesbianism.

29:57.860 --> 29:59.282
Oh, good. Dad's here.

29:59.330 --> 30:01.025
Peter,
you smell like a bar.

30:01.060 --> 30:02.459
That makes sense.

30:02.500 --> 30:06.027
We have to sell the house
and work until we're 80.

30:06.070 --> 30:07.834
Wait, if we sell the house,

30:07.870 --> 30:09.429
where are we going to
have family dinners?

30:09.470 --> 30:11.131
That's what you're
worried about?

30:11.170 --> 30:13.104
I think we can let go of
family dinners at this point.

30:13.140 --> 30:15.529
No one ever really appreciated
all the work I put in.

30:15.580 --> 30:17.207
So I, for one,
would like to be done.

30:17.240 --> 30:20.949
You can't be done, Ida.
That's now how family works.

30:20.980 --> 30:21.970
Wait!

30:22.020 --> 30:24.079
If we sell our house,
where am I going to live?

30:24.120 --> 30:25.884
Dr. Chang: You guys?!

30:25.920 --> 30:29.083
You guys,
this is so awesome!

30:29.120 --> 30:31.088
And you even got me a banner.

30:31.130 --> 30:34.521
Whoa!
Sexy doctor alert!

30:34.560 --> 30:37.222
Hey, I'm here with someone,
she's outside.

30:37.260 --> 30:39.194
Not serious.
But she does exist.

30:39.230 --> 30:42.131
Okay!
Everybody outside --

30:42.170 --> 30:43.035
now!

30:43.070 --> 30:47.974
<i>* Xk</i>

30:48.010 --> 30:51.002
* You shut me down

30:51.050 --> 30:53.974
* You like the control

30:54.020 --> 30:59.220
* Try to hold it down,
I know the answer *

30:59.250 --> 31:05.428
<i>* I can shake it off
and you feel threatened by me *</i>

31:05.460 --> 31:06.950
* I tried to play it nice
but *

31:06.990 --> 31:09.550
* Oh-oh-oh, ooh, ooh

31:09.600 --> 31:10.897
* Don't kill my vibe

31:10.930 --> 31:13.900
As I watch my cocktail napkin
speech blow in the wind,

31:13.940 --> 31:17.968
it dawned on me this could be
one of those epic movie moments

31:18.010 --> 31:19.330
where the heroine's speech

31:19.370 --> 31:21.429
brings her entire family
back together.

31:21.480 --> 31:22.572
* Don't you

31:22.610 --> 31:24.078
* Don't kill my vibe

31:24.110 --> 31:26.249
* I tried to play it nice but

31:26.280 --> 31:29.079
* Oh-oh-oh, ooh, ooh

31:29.120 --> 31:32.647
* Don't kill my vibe

31:32.690 --> 31:35.216
* Oh-oh-oh, ooh, ooh

31:35.260 --> 31:37.683
* Don't break my stride

31:37.720 --> 31:40.519
* Don't kill my vibe

31:40.560 --> 31:44.064
Most people think death
is the opposite of life.

31:44.100 --> 31:45.329
But it's not.

31:45.370 --> 31:49.295
Death is the opposite of...
something.

31:49.340 --> 31:52.970
Life is a circle,
and if that's true,

31:53.010 --> 31:56.332
why are we
so obsessed with...

31:56.380 --> 31:57.700
making progress?

31:57.740 --> 32:00.141
This was not a movie moment.

32:04.590 --> 32:06.479
Thank you, Dr. Chang.

32:06.520 --> 32:08.181
Whoo!

32:10.460 --> 32:12.679
Thank you, Stella.
That was, uh...

32:12.730 --> 32:14.152
a speech.

32:14.200 --> 32:16.123
Stella, what was that?
Are you on drugs? No.

32:16.160 --> 32:19.198
Well...yes, I was
when I wrote this, but--

32:19.230 --> 32:21.164
Relax, Mom, it's just weed.

32:21.200 --> 32:22.998
No, that is
a gateway drug.

32:23.040 --> 32:26.101
Who are you to lecture anybody
on acceptable behavior, Ida?

32:26.140 --> 32:27.539
Peter, I know how you
must feel, but--

32:27.570 --> 32:29.106
Do you, Poppy?

32:29.140 --> 32:30.278
You have any idea
how hard it is

32:30.310 --> 32:32.972
to watch the love of your life
leave you?

32:33.010 --> 32:36.310
Or what it feels like to think
at least if she was with a man,

32:36.350 --> 32:38.079
I could beat
the crap out of him?

32:38.120 --> 32:39.679
Oh, that is mature.

32:39.720 --> 32:43.088
As usual, you will do anything
other than be vulnerable.

32:43.120 --> 32:45.054
What do you want to hear,
Ida?!

32:45.090 --> 32:47.388
That I've been scared every day
for the last eights years

32:47.430 --> 32:50.991
because I thought we were
gonna lose our little girl?

32:51.030 --> 32:52.566
Because I was.

32:52.600 --> 32:56.138
You didn't have
a monopoly on grief,

32:56.170 --> 32:58.036
But unlike you,
I didn't have the luxury

32:58.070 --> 32:59.469
of wearing my heart
on my sleeve

32:59.510 --> 33:03.105
because someone had to be
strong for our kids!

33:03.140 --> 33:04.369
And you may not
want to admit it,

33:04.410 --> 33:07.209
but you needed me to be
strong for you, too.

33:07.250 --> 33:09.309
I wanted to feel like
we were in it together.

33:09.350 --> 33:11.182
You want to be in it
together?

33:11.220 --> 33:13.484
Stop getting naked
with family friends!

33:13.520 --> 33:16.217
Okay, guys!

33:16.260 --> 33:19.025
You both did the best
you could to get

33:19.060 --> 33:22.325
through an impossible
situation -- you all did.

33:22.360 --> 33:25.421
That's -- That's what I was
trying to say in my speech.

33:25.470 --> 33:27.199
That's what
you were going for?

33:27.230 --> 33:30.029
'Cause that did not
come across at all.

33:30.070 --> 33:32.038
The point is...

33:32.070 --> 33:34.732
our problems are fixable.

33:34.780 --> 33:36.600
Mom, Dad...

33:36.640 --> 33:40.042
deep down, you still
really love each other,

33:40.080 --> 33:41.343
and you can
work this out.

33:41.380 --> 33:43.109
Aiden,

33:43.150 --> 33:44.311
you deserve
to be in a relationship

33:44.350 --> 33:46.318
with someone
who is not married.

33:46.350 --> 33:49.183
I-I seriously think it will help
you get your life on track.

33:49.220 --> 33:50.312
I'm sorry, Marlene.

33:50.360 --> 33:52.089
And, Lizzie,
what happened to you?

33:52.130 --> 33:53.689
You used to be so fun,

33:53.730 --> 33:55.698
but now you're so stressed
about your kids and your job.

33:55.730 --> 33:58.665
So you lost a client?
I mean, who cares, so what?

33:58.700 --> 34:00.589
I bet you don't even know
what your firm does.

34:00.630 --> 34:02.598
-Of course I do.
-Of course you do.

34:02.640 --> 34:05.234
I just don't because I know
that this career of yours

34:05.270 --> 34:07.602
is not your real passion.

34:07.640 --> 34:10.199
You used to want to be
a writer, remember?

34:10.239 --> 34:13.244
Writing made you so happy.

34:13.280 --> 34:14.350
So you need to go do that,

34:14.380 --> 34:16.109
because you are not happy,
Lizzie.

34:16.150 --> 34:17.311
Well, how could I be?

34:17.350 --> 34:20.411
Your cancer always
came before my happiness.

34:20.449 --> 34:22.110
Yes, writing used
to make me happy,

34:22.159 --> 34:25.551
but I gave that up when I gave
up a scholarship to Columbia

34:25.590 --> 34:27.752
to stay here and help
take care of you.

34:27.790 --> 34:29.121
Sweetheart.

34:29.159 --> 34:32.369
What?

34:32.400 --> 34:35.233
I didn't know about that.
Of course you didn't.

34:35.270 --> 34:38.308
Because it was our job
to make your life beautiful.

34:38.340 --> 34:40.661
But behind the scenes,
we were a mess.

34:40.710 --> 34:42.303
Look at Aiden.

34:42.340 --> 34:44.342
The thought of losing somebody
he cared about made him

34:44.380 --> 34:46.268
stop caring about
anything at all.

34:46.310 --> 34:48.210
I feel like you're
psychoanalyzing me

34:48.250 --> 34:49.672
unnecessarily,

34:49.719 --> 34:51.141
and I'm good, guys.

34:51.190 --> 34:53.181
I'm great.

34:53.219 --> 34:55.518
In fact, I've nevell\'/I been better.
an: Stay away from Marlene!

34:55.560 --> 34:56.789
What?

35:01.330 --> 35:02.752
Oh, God, Aiden!

35:02.800 --> 35:06.293
<i>* Xk</i>

35:06.330 --> 35:09.300
I
-Aiden!

35:09.340 --> 35:14.301
<i>* Xk</i>

35:17.580 --> 35:18.775
It's starting to happen.
I don't care.

35:18.810 --> 35:20.471
Nelson,
if you leave now,

35:20.510 --> 35:22.239
everything we had
will be perfect forever.

35:22.280 --> 35:26.285
Sara,
life isn't perfect.

35:26.320 --> 35:28.209
It can be beautiful.

35:30.360 --> 35:31.885
Don't you see?

35:31.930 --> 35:36.356
Um, I don't think patients
are allowed to drink wine.

35:36.400 --> 35:39.700
Good thing I'm not
a patient then.

35:39.730 --> 35:41.596
So why are you here?

35:41.640 --> 35:44.666
I like the views of
the city from this window.

35:46.810 --> 35:49.529
And also, when I was sick,
this was my room.

35:52.250 --> 35:54.514
Rough day?

35:54.550 --> 35:57.872
Turns out my...
family's a disaster,

35:57.920 --> 36:02.312
and I can't seem to be
able to fix anything.

36:02.360 --> 36:06.183
My cancer has ruined
my family's lives and...

36:06.230 --> 36:08.551
Oh, my God, I'm complaining
to a cancer patient

36:08.600 --> 36:11.365
about how hard my life is.

36:11.400 --> 36:14.392
You sound like a...

36:14.440 --> 36:18.707
dying girl from one
of these sappy cancer movies.

36:18.740 --> 36:20.629
Trying to fix everybody
else's problems

36:20.670 --> 36:23.230
just so you can avoid
facing your own fears.

36:23.280 --> 36:26.375
That is not
what I'm doing.

36:26.410 --> 36:29.710
That is exactly
what I was doing.

36:29.750 --> 36:33.380
I'm Sadie, by the way.

36:33.420 --> 36:35.388
Hi, Sadie.

36:37.390 --> 36:38.425
I'm Stella.

36:41.460 --> 36:43.428
Look, if you ever want
to talk about anything,

36:43.460 --> 36:46.361
I would be happy to...

36:46.400 --> 36:48.732
just listen.

36:48.770 --> 36:51.501
Just listen.

36:51.540 --> 36:54.271
No, if cancer
taught me one thing...

36:54.310 --> 36:57.439
it's that you can get
through anything...

36:57.480 --> 36:59.608
as long as someone
has your back.

37:03.380 --> 37:05.712
Also, an old guy died
in that bed today,

37:05.750 --> 37:08.219
and I don't think
it's been cleaned.

37:10.390 --> 37:14.327
* If you need to keep

37:14.360 --> 37:15.395
As I walked down the hall,

37:15.430 --> 37:17.751
wishing I had another
bottle of wine,

37:17.800 --> 37:19.290
I couldn't help but wonder,

37:19.330 --> 37:21.367
now that I wasn't sick,

37:21.400 --> 37:24.529
did anyone have my back?

37:24.570 --> 37:26.436
Hey.

37:29.540 --> 37:32.601
Thought I might
find you here.

37:32.650 --> 37:35.449
And that you might
want this.

37:35.480 --> 37:39.314
And then I realized...
he did.

37:39.350 --> 37:43.014
<i>* Xk</i>

37:45.430 --> 37:51.494
* You're the fire
and the flood *

37:51.530 --> 37:56.366
* And I'll always feel you
in my blood *

37:56.400 --> 37:58.562
Yeah, you like that?
I do.

37:58.610 --> 38:00.408
I don't love
the Q&A afterwards.

38:00.440 --> 38:03.501
* Everything is fine

38:03.540 --> 38:06.703
* When your hand is
resting next to mine *

38:06.750 --> 38:08.445
Wow.

38:08.480 --> 38:10.448
Whoa.
I had no idea we could

38:10.480 --> 38:13.381
get so much done
in such a short window.

38:13.420 --> 38:15.309
It that too short?
No.

38:15.360 --> 38:17.385
No, it was hot.
Okay.

38:17.420 --> 38:18.819
You really know
how to get 'er done.

38:18.860 --> 38:20.350
Well...

38:25.900 --> 38:28.460
Listen...

38:28.500 --> 38:30.434
I'm sorry, too.

38:30.470 --> 38:32.359
Sorry, what for?

38:32.410 --> 38:36.005
Not getting to know
the real you.

38:36.040 --> 38:37.929
But I do want to.

38:37.980 --> 38:39.379
And...

38:41.550 --> 38:44.383
...] want you
to know the real me.

38:44.420 --> 38:46.445
And the real me is...

38:46.490 --> 38:48.310
terrified.

38:49.990 --> 38:52.357
What are you terrified of?

38:52.390 --> 38:54.085
The future.

38:57.060 --> 38:58.494
That I'll...

38:58.530 --> 39:00.999
screw it up or waste it.

39:03.500 --> 39:04.433
What I'm really scared of

39:04.470 --> 39:06.768
is that you might not be
okay with all this.

39:09.110 --> 39:14.048
Our forever just got a whole lot
longer than you were expecting.

39:14.080 --> 39:15.445
Stella...

39:15.480 --> 39:18.484
I know I promised you...

39:18.520 --> 39:21.649
that I would love you
for the rest of your life...

39:23.890 --> 39:27.349
I was always gonna love you
for the rest of mine.

39:29.460 --> 39:32.566
You just weren't gonna
be around to see it.

39:32.600 --> 39:34.398
If you really
don't want kids--

39:34.440 --> 39:36.499
I do want kids.

39:38.710 --> 39:41.099
I used to picture myself
with a little girl.

39:43.610 --> 39:44.907
I was just...

39:44.950 --> 39:48.671
I was scared to let myself want
something that I couldn't have.

39:48.720 --> 39:51.417
But, baby,
you can have that now.

39:51.450 --> 39:52.485
What if she gets sick?

39:52.520 --> 39:54.716
Oh, babe, no, no, no.

39:54.760 --> 39:57.513
You can't think like that.

39:57.560 --> 40:00.427
You're not sick anymore.

40:00.460 --> 40:02.497
I promise you...

40:02.530 --> 40:04.089
whatever comes our way,

40:04.130 --> 40:07.862
whatever tomorrow holds...

40:07.900 --> 40:09.595
we'll get through it
together.

40:09.640 --> 40:12.439
Really?
Always.

40:12.470 --> 40:14.438
And I love you so much.

40:14.480 --> 40:15.777
I love you.

40:17.510 --> 40:21.105
So there it was --
the end of my cancer movie...

40:21.150 --> 40:23.915
but the beginning
of my life sentence --

40:23.950 --> 40:26.544
which was full of promise.

40:26.590 --> 40:27.739
* When I was six years old

40:27.790 --> 40:30.452
You sure we can afford for me
to stay at home and write?

40:30.490 --> 40:31.821
Yes.
Yes?

40:31.860 --> 40:33.589
We can't afford
for you not to. Come on.

